{{nihongo|lead=yes|'''Dong Du Japanese Language School'''|ドンズー日本語学校|Donzū Nihongo Gakkō}} is a school that provides [[Japanese language]] and [[Japanese culture|culture]] courses from basic to advanced translation level in [[Phu Nhuan District]], [[Ho Chi Minh City]], [[Vietnam]]. Its main aim is to teach Japanese for Vietnamese people and help students studying abroad in Japan (the two main courses being taken from ''[[Minna no Nihongo]]'' and ''[[Business Kaiwa]]''), but it also provides [[Vietnamese language]] courses for Japanese teachers and individuals who work in Vietnam. Many of the teachers are [[Vietnamese people|Vietnamese]] and [[Japanese people|Japanese]].
Most [[undergraduate]]s in the city and in surrounding [[Provinces of Vietnam|provinces]] take a language course here before joining Japanese universities for studying abroad or working with Japanese companies.

