'''Stanford Online''' is an educational initiative launched by [[Stanford University]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-154808597.html|title=Get master's at Stanford, without going to the Farm|last=Krieger|first=Lisa|date=21 November 2006|work=San Jose Mercury News {{Subscription required|via=[[HighBeam Research]]}}|accessdate=25 January 2015}}</ref> which offers ''a variety of professional education opportunities''.<ref>http://online.stanford.edu/about</ref>
As a part of Stanford Online, Stanford University created an open access ''OpenEdX'' platform which offered a variety of [[MOOC|Massive Open Online Courses]] in 2013 but that site is no longer accessible.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Stanford online coursework to be available on new open-source platform {{!}} Stanford Online|url = http://online.stanford.edu/news/2013/09/13/stanford-online-coursework-be-available-new-open-source-platform|website = online.stanford.edu|accessdate = 2016-01-01}}</ref>
