'''''Technology Innovations in Statistics Education''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[scientific journal]] ({{ISSN|1933-4214}}) covering the uses and influences of technology on [[statistics education]] from [[kindergarten]] to [[professional development]].<ref>{{cite book | chapterurl = http://www.ugr.es/~icmi/iase_study/BackgroundpaperGarfield.pdf | title = Developing Students’ Statistical Reasoning | chapter = The Discipline of Statistics Education | author = Joan Garfield and Dani Ben-Zvi | publisher = Springer | doi = 10.1007/978-1-4020-8383-9 }}</ref> It is published by  [[Berkeley Electronic Press]] and edited by Robert Gould, director of the [http://cts.stat.ucla.edu UCLA Center for Statistics Education].

